HEADWORD: Kapok
<hw>Ka*pok"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prob. fr. the native
name.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A silky wool derived from the seeds
of <spn>Ceiba pentandra</spn> (syn. <spn>Eriodendron
anfractuosum</spn>), a bombaceous tree of the East and West
Indies.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

